  "text": "The small angular offset of spokes locates is in 22.5 • + n × 45 • (n = 0, 1, 2, ..., 7) position when the number of spokes is 16. Similarly, the offset is in 30 • + n × 45 • and 22.5 • + n × 45 • (n = 0, 1, 2, ..., [CITATION_1] when the spoke number is 24 and 32, respectively, as shown in Figure 3 . Since the resonator frequency of device is determined by the dimension and position of the rings and support beams, an offset angle adjustment as small as ±(0.1 • -0.7 • ) of spokes position can slightly change the frequency to achieve the mode-matching condition of the resonator.",
